<span id="freeTextContainer8585547438529977877">Very, very well said. I&apos;ve read widely for my age (approaching mid-thirties) and I think Wallace was not just the literary voice of his own generation</span>
  <span id="freeText8585547438529977877" style="display:none">Very, very well said. I've read widely for my age (approaching mid-thirties) and I think Wallace was not just the literary voice of his own generation but also a prophet for mine and perhaps the one after me. He may have called it television, but Dave also saw the danger of cyber-culture and how addictive it can be.</span>
