  <span id="freeText7883998734345850489" style="display:none">I think the "write what you know" theorem is very true, and that DFW followed this law very seriously not just in Jest but in the collection above. He's not only writing about tennis and the tube and rural fairs; he's writing about himself and his relationship to them. And it's clear that Dave knew himself very well. He knew how introspective and smart and genuine he was. He also knew he was just a "regular guy."<br /><br />Too bad we don't have that regular guy around anymore.</span>
